name: AVC171
PRODUCT: MdtC is a transporter that forms a heteromultimer complex with MdtB to form a multidrug transporter. MdtBC is part of the MdtABC-TolC efflux complex. name: AVC171

name: AVC171

name: AVC171
PRODUCT: The MdtG protein also named YceE appears to be a member of the major facilitator superfamily of transporters and it has been reported when overexpressed to increase fosfomycin and deoxycholate resistances. mdtG is a member of the marA-soxS-rob regulon.

name: AVC171
PRODUCT: MsbA is a multidrug resistance transporter homolog from E. coli and belongs to a superfamily of transporters that contain an adenosine triphosphate (ATP) binding cassette (ABC) which is also called a nucleotide-binding domain (NBD). MsbA is a member of the MDR-ABC transporter group by sequence homology. MsbA transports lipid A a major component of the bacterial outer cell membrane and is the only bacterial ABC transporter that is essential for cell viability.

name: AVC171
PRODUCT: Multidrug efflux pump in E. coli. This multidrug efflux system was originally identified as the Cmr/CmlA chloramphenicol exporter.

name: AVC171
PRODUCT: kdpE is a transcriptional activator that is part of the two-component system KdpD/KdpE that is studied for its regulatory role in potassium transport and has been identified as an adaptive regulator involved in the virulence and intracellular survival of pathogenic bacteria. kdpE regulates a range of virulence loci through direct promoter binding.

name: AVC171
PRODUCT: AcrA is a subunit of the AcrAB-TolC multidrug efflux system that in E. coli.

name: AVC171

name: AVC171
PRODUCT: AmpH is a class C ampC-like beta-lactamase and penicillin-binding protein identified in Escherichia coli.

name: AVC171
PRODUCT: A class C ampC beta-lactamase (cephalosporinase) enzyme described in Escherichia coli shown clinically to confer resistance to penicillin-like and cephalosporin-class antibiotics.
